  "prompt": "How do I play gem TD in DOTA2 when there is no internet?",
  "response": "Playing **Gem TD** in **DOTA 2** without an internet connection can be a bit tricky since custom games like Gem TD typically require an internet connection to download and run. However, if you already have Gem TD installed and just want to play offline, here\u2019s how you can try:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Play Gem TD Offline**\n1. **Ensure Gem TD is Already Installed**:\n   - You must have already downloaded and installed the Gem TD custom game on your Dota 2 client while you were online. If not, you\u2019ll need an internet connection to download it first.\n\n2. **Launch Dota 2 in Offline Mode**:\n   - Open **Steam** in offline mode (go to `Steam > Go Offline`).\n   - Launch **Dota 2** from Steam.\n\n3. **Access the Game**:\n   - Once Dota 2 is open, go to the **Custom Games** section.\n   - Look for **Gem TD** in your installed custom games list.\n\n4. **Play the Game**:\n   - Start Gem TD as you normally would. Since the game is already installed, you should be able to play it offline.\n\n---\n\n### **Limitations**:\n- If Gem TD requires updates or additional assets, you\u2019ll need an internet connection.\n- Some features, like leaderboards or multiplayer, won\u2019t work offline.\n- If the game isn\u2019t already installed, you\u2019ll need internet access to download it.\n\n---\n\n### **Alternative Offline TD Games**:\nIf Gem TD doesn\u2019t work offline, you might consider other standalone tower defense games that don\u2019t require an internet connection, such as:\n- **Bloons TD 6**\n- **Kingdom Rush**\n- **Plants vs. Zombies**\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
